RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELLA PALOMA eased back and tucked in behind the pace heading into the first turn to track from the three path, split rivals at the quarter pole, drifted out a bit to be five wide at the top of the stretch, struck the lead near the furlong marker while drifting in just a bit and edged clear. GUN RUNNIN' GAL bobbled ever so slightly at the start, pressed the pace from outside three wide, applied more pressure up the backstretch dueling on even terms, took over about the three-eighths, was outkicked by the winner but clearly second best. VOLTA D'ORO stalked four to five wide, had no extra but fought on to narrowly secure show honors. BROOKLYN GIRL broke a half-step slowly and was encouraged along early but lacking speed, raced outside at the rear caught five wide early, moved out from five to six wide on the far turn, needed more. ELKE LODGE moved straight to the front to dictate terms to the first turn racing off the rail, faced increasing outside pressure up the backstretch, was overtaken near the three-eighths pole and asked to keep pace but lacked the needed response.

ENTRY.NAME: Elke Lodge
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, insd-2path, pressured, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Gun Runnin' Gal
ENTRY.OWNER: A P Stable and Fox Tale Racing Stable
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 3w, led 3/8-1/8, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Bella Paloma
ENTRY.COMMENT: tucked in 3p early, tracked, split 1/4, led 1/8, edged clear

ENTRY.NAME: Volta d'Oro
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, 4-5w, needed more, got show

ENTRY.NAME: Brooklyn Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: 1/2 step slow, urged, outside at rear, 5-6w, needed more

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HELEONORTIZ shifted in three to four wide off the leading pair into the first turn to stalk those while racing off the inside, lost some ground up the backstretch, given some encouragement about the seven-sixteenths then put to stronger urging by the five-sixteenths while advancing, moved out four wide turning for home, took over the lead at the top of the stretch and forged clear. NURSE RACHETT moved straight to the lead to set the pace inside, faced pressure by an outside foe coming to the three-quarters, was headed by that one past the three-eighths, fought on to regain the advantage over that rival but was no match for the winner. CHICA RABIOSA pressed the pace from outside shifting in two to three wide on the first turn, applied more pressure after the opening quarter dueling up the backstretch, put a head in front past the three-eighths, had no extra for the drive. RAVENEL moved out from three to four wide on the first turn racing off the pace and kept well off the inside, continued outside a foe at the back swinging eight wide into upper stretch, ran on but was not a threat. KIRBY broke just a half-step slowly, raced in behind the leader along the inside early on the first turn under a hold, lost ground up the backstretch, shifted six wide turning for home, was never near enough to threaten.

ENTRY.COMMENT: to lead, inside, pressured, headed 3/8, 2nd best

BROOKLYN GIRLEE moved between runners shortly after the start to set the pace with outside pressure and brief inside pressure, dueled inside the eventual winner but off the inside part of the track through the turn, could not kick on with that one but was second best. APPLE SHAKE SHAKE switched outside a rival early, raced outside at the back going four wide on the turn, improved position while no match for the top pair. LADY LANCER was a little bit fractious in the gate, went straight to the front, showed brief speed inside, steadily retreated. PINK SUNSET was urged at the break, chased from off the leading trio, went four wide on the turn, was not a threat. MEDB was urged at the break, shifted in early and ridden along, was not a factor. SEA IMAGE broke a step slowly, lacked early speed racing off the rail, was never near enough to threaten. PER RULING FROM HISA, MEDB WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR CROP VIOLATION.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RATIONALMILLENNIAL settled off the leaders in the three path early, advanced four to five wide on the far turn in range coming to the quarter pole, took command at the top of the stretch making a bid outside, kicked clear. CIRCLE OF COURAGE raced three wide into the first turn and moving to the fore to dictate terms, shifted in leaving that bend, faced outside pressure up the backstretch racing near the rail, was headed by the seven-sixteenths, kept on in the stretch, drifted out a bit late, was no match for the winner but held second. MERGER OF EQUALS settled off the leaders three to four wide, dropped back heading to the far turn, began to pick it up after swinging out six deep for the drive, ran on but just missed place. DOROTHY'S THE BOSS broke in the air, settled into stride at the back, advanced outside foes four abreast late up the backstretch, shifted in on the far turn, raced off the rail into upper stretch then nearer the rail for room and kept on evenly. FORTIBUG stalked from outside four wide, moved forward to press up the backstretch, took a narrow advantage about the seven-sixteenths, put to a drive by the quarter pole, lacked the needed late kick. CRIMSON LILLE raced inside at the rear early, moved out to go two wide and ridden along heading into the far turn, failed to rally. GRASS CUTTER showed brief speed inside, dropped back off the leader chasing from inside, dropped back and faded. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE START DOROTHY'S THE BOSS WAS DECLARED A NON-STARTER WITH WAGERS TO BE REFUNDED INVOLVING THAT RUNNER.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: I LOVE YOU gained forward position along the rail willingly into the first turn to track the pace, advanced rapidly to take a narrow lead at the half, began to edge away on the far turn, saw the rider look back a couple times for competition coming into upper stretch, was in hand through the length of the stretch while drawing away under a gallop. CRICKET WEST pressed a rival heading to the first turn as that one went to the lead, was still caught four wide on that bend and eased back to stalk up the backstretch, lost ground to and on the far turn and shifted in for that bend to save ground, kept on in the lane to get up for second inside runners but was not in range of the winner. ASTERS D'ORO moved to the front and shifted in two deep to set the pace, was hounded by rivals inside and out, overtaken coming to the half, weakened thereafter. STARRY HOPE was forwardly-positioned three wide between runners early, stalked the leader up the backstretch, was put to urging three furlongs out, floated out wider for the drive, ran on without a late menace.
